The paper focuses on neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning. Specifically, it proposes a new meta-learning algorithm that merges ideas from one-shot approaches with iterative techniques for learning low-degree sparse Boolean polynomial functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks)
